'''Reinke's space''' is a potential space between the vocal ligament and the overlying mucosa<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Xp4YtqM7Ef8C&pg=PA2265&dq=Reinke+space&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjsy_zJmsHXAhXFCcAKHYGvAmIQ6AEIXzAI#v=onepage&q=Reinke%20space&f=false|title=Basic Clinical Radiobiology, Fifth Edition|last=Joiner|first=Michael C.|last2=Kogel|first2=Albert van der|date=2016-06-15|publisher=CRC Press|isbn=9780340808931|language=en}}</ref>. It is not an empty space, but contains cells, special fibers and [[extracellular matrix]]. It plays an important role in the vibration of the vocal cords. [[Edema]] of this space is called [[Reinke's edema]].
